* Introduction

Python notebooks are environments that can run python code (and much more.)

One of the many notebooks implementations is *Jupyter*:

.link https://jupyter.org/

Jupyter notebooks can be run locally (once installed), or "on the cloud".

The [[https://mybinder.org/][MyBinder]] project allows to create notebooks in the cloud and share them with other enthusiasts.
MyBinder allows to turn, say, a [[https://github.com][GitHub]] repository into a Jupyter notebook.

.link https://mybinder.org
.link https://mybinder.readthedocs.io/en/latest

